# IAM policy for OpenTofu deploys (attach to DataFaceDev or a dedicated `civilai-tofu` user)

Minimum permissions for the **data-api-only** UAT stack. Expand when enabling
`create_platform_http_api`, `create_platform_persistence`, or `create_amplify_app`.

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "EC2DataApi",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ec2:RunInstances",
        "ec2:TerminateInstances",
        "ec2:StartInstances",
        "ec2:StopInstances",
        "ec2:Describe*",
        "ec2:CreateSecurityGroup",
        "ec2:DeleteSecurityGroup",
        "ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupIngress",
        "ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupEgress",
        "ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupIngress",
        "ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupEgress",
        "ec2:CreateTags",
        "ec2:AllocateAddress",
        "ec2:ReleaseAddress",
        "ec2:AssociateAddress",
        "ec2:DisassociateAddress"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    },
    {
      "Sid": "IAMForEC2InstanceProfile",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "iam:CreateRole",
        "iam:DeleteRole",
        "iam:GetRole",
        "iam:PassRole",
        "iam:PutRolePolicy",
        "iam:DeleteRolePolicy",
        "iam:CreateInstanceProfile",
        "iam:DeleteInstanceProfile",
        "iam:AddRoleToInstanceProfile",
        "iam:RemoveRoleFromInstanceProfile",
        "iam:GetInstanceProfile",
        "iam:ListInstanceProfilesForRole",
        "iam:TagRole",
        "iam:TagInstanceProfile"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:iam::379604374458:role/civilai-uat-data-api-role",
        "arn:aws:iam::379604374458:instance-profile/civilai-uat-data-api-profile",
        "arn:aws:iam::379604374458:role/civilai-uat-*",
        "arn:aws:iam::379604374458:instance-profile/civilai-uat-*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Sid": "SSMUatSecrets",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ssm:PutParameter",
        "ssm:GetParameter",
        "ssm:DeleteParameter",
        "ssm:AddTagsToResource"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:ssm:us-east-1:379604374458:parameter/civilai/uat/*"
    },
    {
      "Sid": "StateBackend",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:PutObject",
        "s3:DeleteObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::civilai-tofu-state",
        "arn:aws:s3:::civilai-tofu-state/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Sid": "StateLock",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "dynamodb:GetItem",
        "dynamodb:PutItem",
        "dynamodb:DeleteItem"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:dynamodb:us-east-1:379604374458:table/civilai-tofu-locks"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Apply failed on DataFaceDev (2026-07-09)

`DataFaceDev` can manage S3/DynamoDB (bootstrap succeeded) but lacks:

- `iam:CreateRole`
- `ssm:PutParameter`
- `ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupEgress`

**Next step:** Attach the policy above in IAM (or use an admin role), then:

```bash
cd civil-ai-platform/infra/opentofu/environments/uat
tofu apply
```

Orphan SG `civilai-uat-data-api-sg` may need manual delete if apply left it in a bad state.
